    <item>
      <title>Rigid Body Motion</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_cg/rigidbody/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_cg/rigidbody/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;🔗 See more details about &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ChenYingShan1114/rigid-bodies&#34;&gt;rigid body motion&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ChenYingShan1114/rigid-bodies-contact&#34;&gt;contact&lt;/a&gt;, forked from the projects in physical-based animation course at University of Toronto.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Using projected Gauss-Seidel algorithm to deal with contact effect.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;rigid-body-motion&#34;&gt;Rigid Body Motion&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/RigidBody/rigidbodymotion.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;      &#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;rigid-body-contact&#34;&gt;Rigid Body Contact&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/RigidBody/rigidbodycontact.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;    &#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;reference&#34;&gt;Reference&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X0spyNYoZ1o&amp;list=PLTkE7n2CwG_PH09_q0Q7ttjqE2F9yGeM3&amp;index=9&#34;&gt;Physics-based animation lecture 7: Rigid Bodies (Updated Again)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8fFg7fOAHSA&amp;list=PLTkE7n2CwG_PH09_q0Q7ttjqE2F9yGeM3&amp;index=10&#34;&gt;Physics-based animation lecture 9: Rigid Bodies Contact&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1RF7j-Yc21c&amp;t=500s&#34;&gt;Rotation Matrix Time Derivative&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Cloth Simulation</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_cg/clothsimulation/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_cg/clothsimulation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;🔗 See more details about &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ChenYingShan1114/cloth-simulation&#34;&gt;cloth simulation&lt;/a&gt;, forked from the projects in physical-based animation course at University of Toronto.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Using co-rotational linear elasticity energy model.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;linearly-implicit-euler-method&#34;&gt;Linearly Implicit Euler Method&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/ClothSimulation/cloth-linearly.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;    &#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;with-collistion&#34;&gt;With Collistion&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/ClothSimulation/cloth-linearly-collision.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;    &#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;fully-implicit-with-gradient-descent&#34;&gt;Fully Implicit with Gradient Descent&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/ClothSimulation/cloth-gradient_descent.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;    &#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;fully-implicit-with-newton-method&#34;&gt;Fully Implicit with Newton Method&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/ClothSimulation/cloth-newton.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;    &#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;reference&#34;&gt;Reference&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MJj17gpmrI4&amp;list=PLTkE7n2CwG_PH09_q0Q7ttjqE2F9yGeM3&amp;index=8&#34;&gt;Physics-based animation lecture 6: Cloth Simulation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gemini.google.com/app/6d549414b840ab0d&#34;&gt;Gemini Note&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Finite Element Method</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_cg/finiteelementmethod/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_cg/finiteelementmethod/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;🔗 See more details about &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ChenYingShan1114/finite-element-method&#34;&gt;finite element method&lt;/a&gt;, forked from the projects in physical-based animation course at University of Toronto.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Using neo-Hookean strain energy function.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;linearly-implicit-euler-method&#34;&gt;Linearly Implicit Euler Method&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;stanford-bunny&#34;&gt;Stanford Bunny&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;coarse-tetrahedral-grid&#34;&gt;Coarse Tetrahedral Grid&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/FiniteElementMethod/fem-linearly-bunny.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;coarse-tetrahedral-grid-with-high-poly-skinning&#34;&gt;Coarse Tetrahedral Grid with High Poly Skinning&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/FiniteElementMethod/fem-linearly-bunny-skinning.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;armadillo&#34;&gt;Armadillo&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;coarse-tetrahedral-grid-1&#34;&gt;Coarse Tetrahedral Grid&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/FiniteElementMethod/fem-linearly-arma.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;coarse-tetrahedral-grid-with-high-poly-skinning-1&#34;&gt;Coarse Tetrahedral Grid with High Poly Skinning&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/FiniteElementMethod/fem-linearly-arma-skinning.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;fully-implicit-with-newton-method&#34;&gt;Fully Implicit with Newton Method&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;armadillo-1&#34;&gt;Armadillo&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;coarse-tetrahedral-grid-2&#34;&gt;Coarse Tetrahedral Grid&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/FiniteElementMethod/fem-newton-arma.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;!-- * ### Cube&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/MassSpringSystem/3d-mass-spring-cube.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Mass Spring Systems</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_cg/massspringsystem/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 15 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_cg/massspringsystem/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;🔗 See more details about &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ChenYingShan1114/1d-mass-spring-system&#34;&gt;1D&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ChenYingShan1114/3d-mass-spring-system&#34;&gt;3D&lt;/a&gt; mass spring systems&lt;/a&gt;, forked from the projects in physical-based animation course at University of Toronto.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;1d-mass-spring-system-with-different-algorithms&#34;&gt;1D Mass Spring System with Different Algorithms&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;forward-euler&#34;&gt;Forward Euler&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/MassSpringSystem/1d-mass-spring-forward-euler.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;backward-euler&#34;&gt;Backward Euler&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/MassSpringSystem/1d-mass-spring-backward-euler.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;symplectic-euler&#34;&gt;Symplectic Euler&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/MassSpringSystem/1d-mass-spring-symplectic-euler.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;runge-kutta&#34;&gt;Runge-Kutta&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/MassSpringSystem/1d-mass-spring-runge-kutta.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;3d-mass-spring-system-with-different-models&#34;&gt;3D Mass Spring System with Different Models&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;cube&#34;&gt;Cube&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/MassSpringSystem/3d-mass-spring-cube.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;cylinder&#34;&gt;Cylinder&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/MassSpringSystem/3d-mass-spring-cylinder.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;stanford-bunny&#34;&gt;Stanford Bunny&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;video src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/self/mp4/projects_cg/MassSpringSystem/3d-mass-spring-bunny.mov&#34; controls type=&#34;video/mov&#34; width=&#34;600&#34;&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;reference&#34;&gt;Reference&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5j37DOD8q4U&amp;list=PLTkE7n2CwG_PH09_q0Q7ttjqE2F9yGeM3&amp;index=2&#34;&gt;Physics_based Animation Lecture 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wpZe1PI7uhQ&amp;list=PLTkE7n2CwG_PH09_q0Q7ttjqE2F9yGeM3&amp;index=3&#34;&gt;Physics-Based Animation Lecture 2: Time Integration&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9DcKg77nQBA&amp;list=PLTkE7n2CwG_PH09_q0Q7ttjqE2F9yGeM3&amp;index=5&#34;&gt;Physics-Based Animation Lecture 3: Mass-Spring Systems in 3D&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Dynamics of Human Locomotion</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_animation/locomotions/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 30 Mar 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_animation/locomotions/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h6&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linkedin.com/learning/character-animation-locomotion&#34;&gt; Linkedin learning course &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2&gt; Between the Velocity &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;The difference between jogging and sprinting is not merely a matter of speed. It also lies in how the body stores and releases force through the joints during movement.&#xA;&lt;p&gt;• When jogging, the joints store less force, the motion is more rhythmic and relaxed, the body’s center of gravity remains stable, and the arm swing is minimal.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;• In contrast, during sprinting, the knee and ankle joints store significantly more force, the center of gravity shifts forward, and the arms swing with greater intensity to generate forward momentum.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Solitude House</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_animation/scene/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 30 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_animation/scene/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The lonely house in this piece symbolizes both physical isolation and a deeper sense of inner solitude. For me, loneliness is not just an absence of company. It’s a rare opportunity to engage in quiet, honest conversations with myself. In solitude, I’m able to calmly explore my inner world, allowing my thoughts to expand, my emotions to settle, and my perspective to deepen. It’s in these moments of stillness that I often find new strength, clarity, and resilience to face life with greater purpose.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>My First Step into Animation: Cartoon Rocket Launch</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_animation/rocket/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Apr 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/projects_animation/rocket/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The launch of a rocket is often seen as a symbol of venturing into the unknown, which is an idea that resonates deeply with my own journey as I step into the world of animation. This short film serves as a personal metaphor, with the rocket representing my ambitions and curiosity at the very beginning of this creative path.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The rocket is designed in a simple, cartoon style, reflecting the innocence and rawness of someone just starting out. While the design remains playful, the animation is brought to life through dynamic smoke effects created using Maya&amp;rsquo;s particle system, which adds a sense of timing, weight, and immersion to the scene.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
